## Summary of Changes

| # | Issue | Fix |
|---|-------|-----|
| 1 | No security headers | Added `helmet()` |
| 2 | No body-size limit | `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })` |
| 3 | No rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` middleware |
| 4 | No input validation | Validate & parse query params in `/users` |
| 5 | No global error handler | 4-arg `(err, req, res, next)` middleware |
| 6 | No 404 handler | Catch-all returning JSON (not HTML) |
| 7 | Stack traces leaked | Conditionally expose details only in `development` |
| 8 | Hardcoded port | Use `process.env.PORT` with fallback |
| 9 | Server starts on import | Guard with `require.main === module` |

**New dependencies to install:**
```bash
npm install helmet express-rate-limit
```

